哇 涡旋纹花呢衫

144
00:08:20,086 --> 00:08:22,758
It goes with my corduroy suit.
那件是用来配我的灯芯绒西服

145
00:08:23,101 --> 00:08:26,006
if you mean it should end up in
the same place, then I agree.
如果你觉得它该和那西服同归于尽
我也同意

146
00:08:27,404 --> 00:08:29,555
Is this your only tie?
这是你唯一的一条领带?

147
00:08:30,596 --> 00:08:33,474
Technically, yes. But, if you'll notice...
理论上来说 是的
但是 如果你能注意到...

148
00:08:34,324 --> 00:08:36,174
It's reversible!
它是正反两面的!

149
00:08:38,339 --> 00:08:40,024
So it works as two.
可以当两条用

150
00:08:40,093 --> 00:08:42,998
Sweetie, I don't even think it works as one.
亲爱的 我觉得当一条用它都够呛

151
00:08:44,804 --> 00:08:46,466
- Is this all your clothes?
- Eh, yeah.
- 这就是你全部的衣服了?
- 没错

152
00:08:46,492 --> 00:08:48,383
Everything since the eighth grade.
八年级至今的全部衣服都在这儿了

153
00:08:48,506 --> 00:08:51,329
- The eighth grade?
- My last growth sprout
- 八年级?
- 我最后发育的年龄

154
00:08:53,453 --> 00:08:56,523
Ok, well, let's go back to the curdoroy suit.
好吧 还是选这套灯芯绒西服吧

155
00:08:56,564 --> 00:08:58,510
- Great.
- Yeah.
- 棒极了
- 是啊

156
00:09:00,181 --> 00:09:02,028
I said no. Put it down.
我说了不 把它放下

157
00:09:07,937 --> 00:09:09,965
Hey Sheldon.
嗨 Sheldon

158
00:09:10,226 --> 00:09:11,486
Hello Penny.
你好 Penny

159
00:09:12,994 --> 00:09:14,912
Get anything good?
收到啥好东西了?

160
00:09:16,557 --> 00:09:20,010
Just the latest copy of
Applied Particle Physics quarterly.
只是最新的应用粒子物理学季刊

161
00:09:20,078 --> 00:09:23,326
Oh, you know, that is so weird
that yours came and mine didn't.
哦 那真是有点奇怪
你的到了可我那期还没来

162
00:09:29,109 --> 00:09:30,685
It was a joke.
我在开玩笑

163
00:09:34,946 --> 00:09:36,837
Yep.
是的

164
00:09:37,043 --> 00:09:39,496
Tip you waitresses.
I'm here all week.
打赏你的服务员
我整星期都会在这里哦

165
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:42,647
Penny, just to save you from further awkwardness,
Penny 为了防止你进一步尴尬

166
00:09:42,716 --> 00:09:46,169
know that I'm perfectly comfortable with
the two of us climbing the stairs in silence.
我并不介意
我们俩爬楼梯时保持沉默

167
00:09:46,416 --> 00:09:48,951
Oh, yeah ok, me too. Zip it, lock it.
好 我也是
拉链拉上 锁住

168
00:09:51,691 --> 00:09:52,884
Put it in your pocket.
放进你的口袋

169
00:09:57,282 --> 00:09:59,790
- So, you and Leonard...
- Oh dear God...
- 那么 你和Leonard...
- 老天啊...

170
00:10:00,491 --> 00:10:02,091
Little misunderstanding, huh?
一点小误会啊?

171
00:10:02,618 --> 00:10:03,940
A little misunderstanding...?
一点小误会...?

172
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:07,305
Galileo and the Pope had a little misunderstanding.
伽利略和罗马教皇也有一点小误会
(伽利略因日心说被教皇迫害)

173
00:10:10,969 --> 00:10:14,794
Anyway, I was talking to Leonard this morning
and I think he feels really bad about it.
不管怎样 今天早上我跟Leonard谈过
我感觉他很难过

174
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:18,513
How do you feel?
你有什么感觉?

175
00:10:19,878 --> 00:10:21,329
I don't understand the question.
我不明白你的问题

176
00:10:22,779 --> 00:10:26,087
I'm just asking if it's difficult
to be fighting with your best friend.
我只想问
跟自己最好的朋友作对 会不会很难?

177
00:10:27,526 --> 00:10:29,397
I haven't thought about it like that.
我没有这么想过

178
00:10:29,677 --> 00:10:32,567
I wonder if I've been experiencing physiological manifestations
我只是在想
这些无意识的情感波动

179
00:10:32,687 --> 00:10:35,230
of some sort of unconscious emotional turmoil
会不会影响我的生理表现

180
00:10:36,626 --> 00:10:37,655
Wait, what?
等等 你说什么?

181
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:39,618
I couldn't poop this morning.
今天早上拉不出大便

182
00:10:44,149 --> 00:10:47,079
You should just talk to him,
I'm sure you guys can work this out.
你得找他谈谈 我肯定你们俩能和好

183
00:10:47,458 --> 00:10:50,236
- Certainly preferable to my plan.
- Which was?
- 我的计划更可取
- 你的计划是?

184
00:10:50,626 --> 00:10:52,046
A powerful laxative.
一服轻泻剂

185
00:10:54,265 --> 00:10:56,427
You absolutely should talk to him.
你真该找他谈谈

186
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,018
Look, I know Leonard values you
as a friend and he told me himself
我知道Leonard当你是朋友
而且他自己说的 如果没有你的小点子

187
00:10:59,226 --> 00:11:02,698
without your little idea there's no way
he could come up with this whole experiment thing.
他根本无法提出这个实验

188
00:11:07,032 --> 00:11:08,749
Excuse me. "Little idea"?
对不起 "小点子"?

189
00:11:08,994 --> 00:11:10,761
Yeah, I mean he tried to explain it to me,
是的 他试着跟我解释这个实验

190
00:11:10,881 --> 00:11:12,540
- I didn't really understand it but...
- Of course you didn't.
- 我实在不明白 但是...
- 你当然不明白

191
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:14,210
He said: "Little idea"?
他说"小点子"?

192
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:17,464
Oh, well, no...
Not...
噢 不... 不是...

193
00:11:17,648 --> 00:11:19,974
- Not in those words.
- In what words then, exactly?
- 不是那个词
- 那他是怎么说的?

194
00:11:20,432 --> 00:11:23,393
Oh, you know... Gee. The exact words are...
It's more the spirit in which he said...
你知道的....确切的词是...
他说的更富有灵气...

195
00:11:23,513 --> 00:11:25,934
- What did he say?
- You had a lucky hunch
- 他说了什么?
- 你有个幸运驼背

196
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:29,931
Hey, Sheldon, I've been thinking, instead of arguing about this...
嘿 Sheldon 我在想 与其争论...

197
00:11:30,051 --> 00:11:32,028
Don't you ever speak to me again.
不要再跟我说话

198
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,611
What...?
什么...?

199
00:11:49,692 --> 00:11:51,720
Ok, I'm leaving for the conference.
我要去参加会议了

200
00:11:52,087 --> 00:11:54,420
Have fun presenting my "lucky hunch"
但愿你能尽情陈述我的"幸运驼背"

201
00:11:54,540 --> 00:11:56,254
Shel, I didn't mean it like that.
Shel 我并不是这意思

202
00:11:56,374 --> 00:11:58,040
- Then why did you say it?
- I don't know, I wasn't...
- 那你为什么这么说?
- 我不知道 我...

203
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:01,909
- Were you trying to impress Penny?
- No, no, not at all. A little bit.
- 你想逗Penny开心?
- 不 不 并不是 有一点

204
00:12:03,183 --> 00:12:04,956
How did that work out for you?
那样真的有用吗?

205
00:12:05,244 --> 00:12:08,764
- Leonard, ready to go?
- Libido: 1 Truth: 0.
- Leonard 准备好了吗?
- 性欲:1  真相:0

206
00:12:11,624 --> 00:12:12,897
Ok, I'm gonna ask you one more time.
我再问你一次

207
00:12:13,017 --> 00:12:15,547
We did the work together,
let's present the paper together.
我们一起做的研究
就一起去陈述论文吧

208
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:17,479
And I'm telling you for the last time,
我最后回答你一次

209
00:12:17,599 --> 00:12:20,429
it's pandering, it's undignifying, and bite me.
这是在拉皮条 这是无地自容
有种咬我

210
00:12:22,818 --> 00:12:23,823
Let's go.
我们走吧

211
00:12:24,061 --> 00:12:25,943
- Bye Sheldon.
- Goodbye Penny.
- 再见 Sheldon
- 再见 Penny

212
00:12:37,162 --> 00:12:38,721
One of these days... bshh!
总有那么一天...卟!

213
00:12:42,282 --> 00:12:43,287
There you go.
可以了

214
00:12:43,586 --> 00:12:45,072
You're right this side does look better.
你说的对 这一面的确好看点

215
00:12:45,329 --> 00:12:48,095
No, no, I didn't say better, I said "less stained".
不 我并没说更好看
我说"少点污渍"

216
00:12:50,209 --> 00:12:53,084
I just checked the house.
There's probably 20-25 people in there.
我刚刚检查了下房间
里面大约有20-25个人

217
00:12:53,204 --> 00:12:54,700
- You're kidding!
- Is that all?
- 真的?!
- 就这么多?

218
00:12:54,890 --> 00:12:58,229
"All?"
In particle physics 25 is Woodstock!
"就这么多?" 在量子物理学里
25人就是伍德斯托克音乐节

219
00:13:01,562 --> 00:13:03,609
- Then good!
- I wasn't expecting such a crowd,
- 那很好!
- 我可没想到有这么多人

220
00:13:03,729 --> 00:13:04,731
I'm all nervous.
我好紧张

221
00:13:04,851 --> 00:13:07,027
It's ok, just open with a joke,
you'll be fine.
没事的 开头讲个笑话 会顺利的

222
00:13:07,345 --> 00:13:09,246
A joke... Ok.
笑话...好吧

223
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:12,159
How about this? Um, ok...
这个怎么样? 呃 好吧...

224
00:13:12,279 --> 00:13:13,725
There's this farmer
有个农夫

225
00:13:13,994 --> 00:13:17,776
and he has these chickens but they won't lay any eggs, so...
他养了一群鸡却不会下蛋 于是...

226
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:19,897
he calls a physicist to help.
他找了个物理学家来帮忙

227
00:13:20,118 --> 00:13:22,840
The physicist then does some calculations,
物理学家做了些计算

228
00:13:23,092 --> 00:13:26,430
and he says: "I have a solution,
然后说 "我有个解决的办法"

229
00:13:26,797 --> 00:13:31,008
but it only works for spherical chickens in a vacuum".
"但只对在真空环境下的球形鸡适用"

230
00:13:33,569 --> 00:13:34,574
Right?
好笑吧?

231
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:41,509
Oh, sorry, I just had heard it before.
噢 对不起 我之前听过这个笑话

232
00:13:42,216 --> 00:13:45,262
- Let's roll. Hey, nice suit.
- It's a classic, right?
- 我们进去 嘿 不错的西服
- 很经典 对吧?

233
00:13:46,746 --> 00:13:49,147
I really should have brought my own car.
我真该自己开车来

234
00:13:51,761 --> 00:13:53,351
So, in conclusion,
总而言之

235
00:13:53,471 --> 00:13:56,251
the data show that at temperatures approaching absolute zero,
数据显示 当温度接近绝对零度时

236
00:13:56,371 --> 00:13:59,870
the moment of inertia changes, and a solid becomes a supersolid,
惯性矩会改变 固体将变成超立体

237
00:13:59,990 --> 00:14:04,011
which clearly appears to be a previously unknown state of matter.
也就是我们之前所未知的物态

238
00:14:06,913 --> 00:14:08,003
Thank you!
谢谢!

239
00:14:13,169 --> 00:14:15,216
- Are there any questions?
- Yeah.
- 有什么问题吗?
- 有

240
00:14:15,449 --> 00:14:17,210
What the hell was that?
那是什么鬼东西?

241
00:14:19,851 --> 00:14:20,941
Any other questions?
还有其他问题吗?

242
00:14:21,545 --> 00:14:26,097
Doctor Sheldon Cooper here, I am
the lead author of this particular paper.
我是Sheldon Cooper博士
是这篇论文的主笔

243
00:14:27,785 --> 00:14:28,820
Thank you.
谢谢

244
00:14:30,832 --> 00:14:35,225
And you sir, you have completely skipped
over the part where I was walking through the park
而你 这位先生
你完全跳过了那段 -- 我穿过公园

245
00:14:35,488 --> 00:14:38,615
and I saw these children on a
merry-go-round which started me thinking
看到孩子们在旋转木马上

246
00:14:38,735 --> 00:14:41,532
about the moment of inertia in gases like helium
引起我思考当类似氦气的气体

247
00:14:41,652 --> 00:14:43,590
at temperatures approaching absolute zero.
温度达到绝对零度时的惯性矩

248
00:14:43,710 --> 00:14:46,512
I didn't skip it. It's just
an anecdote, it's not science.
我没有跳过 那只是个趣闻 并不是科学

249
00:14:46,632 --> 00:14:49,626
Oh, I see. It was
the apple falling on Newton's head,
噢 我知道了
那是掉在牛顿头上的苹果

250
00:14:49,746 --> 00:14:52,314
- was that just an anecdote?
- You are not Isaac Newton.
- 那只是个趣闻吗?
- 你不是艾萨克・牛顿

251
00:14:52,434 --> 00:14:55,751
No, no, that's true. Gravity
would have been apparent to me without the apple.
不 不 这是真的
不用苹果 重力也能找到我

252
00:14:56,543 --> 00:14:58,241
You cannot possibly be that arrogant.
你怎么能如此傲慢

253
00:14:58,361 --> 00:15:00,720
You continue to underestimate me,
my good man.
你就继续低估我吧 伙计

254
00:15:01,315 --> 00:15:05,189
Look, if you weren't happy with my presentation
then maybe you should have given it with me!
听着 如果你因为我的陈述而不愉快
也许你该跟我一起陈述!

255
00:15:05,202 --> 00:15:07,235
As I have explained repeatedly,
unlike you,
我已经重复过好几次 跟你不同

256
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,698
I don't need validation from lesser minds.
我不需要那些没脑子的人来肯定我

257
00:15:09,728 --> 00:15:10,546
No offense.
无意冒犯

258
00:15:11,109 --> 00:15:12,318
Really, so why did you come?
真的? 那你为什么来?

259
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:13,774
Because I knew you'd screw this up.
因为我知道你会搞砸

260
00:15:13,796 --> 00:15:15,129
I didn't screw it up!
我并没有搞砸!

261
00:15:15,142 --> 00:15:17,557
Oh, please. I admit that spherical
chicken joke,
拜托 我承认那个球形鸡的笑话不错

262
00:15:17,579 --> 00:15:18,568
- that was hilarious.
- Thank you.
- 很搞笑
- 谢谢

263
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,506
But it was straight downhill from there.
但从那以后就直线下滑

264
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:22,804
I've had enough of your condescendship.
我受够了你的鄙视

265
00:15:22,904 --> 00:15:25,875
Maybe I didn't go to college
when I was 11 like you.
也许我没有像你一样 11岁就上大学

266
00:15:25,888 --> 00:15:29,373
Maybe I got my doctorate at
24 instead of 16
也许我24岁才获得博士学位
而不是16岁

267
00:15:29,393 --> 00:15:31,100
but you are not the only person
who is smarter than
但你不是唯一一个

268
00:15:31,113 --> 00:15:32,507
everyone else in this room!
比这里在座各位聪明的人!

269
00:15:33,887 --> 00:15:34,497
No offense.
无意冒犯

270
00:15:36,566 --> 00:15:38,326
And I am clearly not the only person
而且我显然不是唯一一个

271
00:15:38,351 --> 00:15:40,117
who is tormented by insecurity
被不安全感折磨

272
00:15:40,136 --> 00:15:42,244
and has an ego in need of constant validation!
并需要被持续认可的自负的人!

273
00:15:42,385 --> 00:15:43,984
So you admit you're an egotist?
你承认自己自负了?

274
00:15:44,218 --> 00:15:44,995
Yes!
是的!

275
00:15:46,401 --> 00:15:49,389
My name is doctor Leonard Hofstadter
and I can never please my parents so
我是Leonard Hofstadter博士
我永远取悦不了我的父母

276
00:15:49,395 --> 00:15:51,768
I need all my self esteem
from strangers like you!
所以我需要从你们这些陌生人身上
找回自尊!

277
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:52,869
But he's worse!
但他更糟糕!

278
00:15:53,421 --> 00:15:54,778
Ok, that's it!
好了 够了!

279
00:15:55,169 --> 00:15:55,722
Stop it!
停下!

280
00:15:58,423 --> 00:16:01,023
You cannot blow up my head
with your mind!
用你的意念弄不爆我的脑袋!

281
00:16:01,236 --> 00:16:02,956
Then I'll settle for your aneurism!
那么我就让你生块动脉瘤!

282
00:16:03,518 --> 00:16:05,142
- Stop it!
- You hit me!
- 停下!
- 你打我?!

283
00:16:05,247 --> 00:16:06,397
You saw that he hit me!
你们看到了 他打我!

284
00:16:06,563 --> 00:16:08,025
You tried to blow up my head!
你想弄爆我的脑袋!

285
00:16:08,057 --> 00:16:08,962
So it was working!
那就是说有用咯!

286
00:16:08,994 --> 00:16:11,348
It wa... It was not!
You're a nutcase!
没...没有用! 你是个疯子!

287
00:16:11,368 --> 00:16:12,324
We'll see about that!
我们走着瞧!

288
00:16:12,469 --> 00:16:13,817
Heads up, you people in the front row!
戴好头盔! 你们坐在前排的人

289
00:16:13,821 --> 00:16:15,053
This is a splash zone!
这里是浪溅带!

290
00:16:16,209 --> 00:16:16,864
Stop it!
住手!

291
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:17,839
Just quit it!
快住手!

292
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,240
Is this usually how these physics things go?
物理学通常都是发展成这样的吗?

293
00:16:26,687 --> 00:16:27,926
More often than you think.
比你能想象的要多

294
00:16:44,541 --> 00:16:46,326
You could have offered me a ride home.
你本可以载我一程的

295
00:16:48,258 --> 00:16:49,998
You're lucky I didn't run you over.
没有轧死你 已经算你走运了

296
00:16:51,101 --> 00:16:52,987
I really don't understand what you're so unhappy about.
真不知道你为什么这么不开心

297
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,650
You begged me to come, I came.
你求我去的 我去了

298
00:16:54,678 --> 00:16:55,853
There's just no pleasing you.
你这人真难伺候

299
00:16:56,858 --> 00:16:59,412
You're right, I'm the problem,
I'm the one that needs help.
你说的对 问题出在我身上
我才是需要帮助的人

300
00:16:59,881 --> 00:17:02,089
Well, that's not much of
an apology but I'll take it.
好吧 虽然这算不上道歉 但我接受

301
00:17:03,274 --> 00:17:04,487
Excuse me,
不好意思

302
00:17:05,026 --> 00:17:07,299
is there anything you would apologise for?
你有什么需要道歉吗?

303
00:17:08,897 --> 00:17:09,513
Yes.
有

304
00:17:10,653 --> 00:17:12,810
I'm sorry I tried to blow up your head.
很抱歉我尝试弄爆你的头

305
00:17:14,780 --> 00:17:15,884
It was uncalled for.
很不必要的举动

306
00:17:17,328 --> 00:17:18,304
You won't believe this.
你们不会相信的

